article.headline: Lafayette 83, La Salle 63
article.story: EASTON, Pa. (AP) -- Winston Davis had 19 points and nine rebounds and Lafayette shot over 60 percent from the field in its 83-63 win over La Salle on Saturday. Senior guard Justin Deberry had 15 points and scored the 1,000th of his career on the opening possession for Lafayette (2-1). Jermaine Thomas and Steven Smith each had 16 points for La Salle (0-4.) Lafayette made nine of its first 12 shots from the floor, including its first seven 3-point attempts, to build a 30-14 lead in the middle of the first half. La Salle reduced the lead to 36-30 at the half. In the second half, a 3-pointer by DeBerry sparked a 20-3 run that helped Lafayette pull away. La Salle shot 38 percent from the floor and lost the rebound battle 36-23. Mike Farrell finished with 13 points and six rebounds for La Salle, while Rasheed Quadri scored 10.
